**Conventions:** "the file/plan" = current working file. "list of issues" = issues from last `review`/`fix-silent` pass, in report order; `fiximportant` takes topmost remaining. `timeout_sleep_ints` = no-op for files without timeout/sleep vars. "Clean" (`cleanstop`) = no content-changing edits in last pass.

**Naming:** Workers — hyphen-case, exhaustive single-pass. Families — snake_case, wrap a worker in `timeout_sleep_ints`/`cleanstop`, accept `max=N`. Loop functions — hyphen-case, process the issue list one item at a time, built-in cap.

**Pipeline family pattern** (`max=1` default; invoke `<family> max=N`): (1) `timeout_sleep_ints` (2) worker (3) final step (4) if `max>1`: `cleanstop`, else repeat from step 2 up to `max−1` more times.

| Family | Worker | Final | Cap |
|---|---|---|---|
| `fix` | `fix-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `broad` | `fix-broad-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `security` | `fix-security-silent` | `linesme` | 5 |
| `perf_review` | `fix-perf-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `api_review` | `fix-api-review-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `md_update` | `md-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |
| `schema` | `schema-update-silent` | `showme` | 4 |

`sequential-fixes` is a loop (not a family): `fiximportant; cleanstop, else fiximportant again` ×10 max.

**One true file (always):** copy any file to a single working path immediately; all edits go there; `cp` working→outputs only when presenting; never edit the presented copy; view the working path immediately before every `str_replace`.

**Describe:** `describe-behavior` — one-sentence job, capability bullets with specific numbers, CLI flags, line count + deps; don't trust the docstring. `describe-structure` — entry point, call hierarchy, state machines, exception flow, external interfaces; flag docstring divergence; group workarounds by root cause. `describe-structure-deep` — same but exhaustive: every workaround, its forcing constraint, shared-root siblings, and the clean design.

**Plan:** `plan-review-api` — API-expert review (surface area, naming, defaults, error contracts); no edits. `plan-simplify-silent` — cut overspecified/redundant/speculative/duplicate; collapse, generalize, drop; iterate until further cuts lose load-bearing content; no commentary. `simplify-plan` — `plan-simplify-silent` + report line count and what was cut. `simplify-plan-deeper` — `simplify-plan` ×3 max if cuts were made. `plan-score` — score 5 categories × sub-metrics (1–5): API quality, implementation clarity, test coverage, risk management, doc quality; identify highest-leverage changes; comparison table if a prior version exists.

**Filesystem:** `showskillfs` — ls /mnt/skills/{public,examples,user}/. `showtranscriptfs` — ls /mnt/transcripts/. `showprojectfs` — ls /mnt/project. `showuserfs` — ls /home/claude/, outputs/, uploads/, tool_results. `showmyfs` — showuserfs + showskillfs + showtranscriptfs + showprojectfs. `mtime_output` — outputs/ files with MDT mtimes. `mtime_claude` — same for /home/claude/. `showhotfs` — list "hot" files (created/modified this chat) in /home/claude/ + outputs/: md5 each, classify CREATED (no same-name in uploads//mnt/project) / MODIFIED (exists but md5 differs; show origin md5) / COLD-COPY (md5 == an original); bucket regenerable artifacts (*.zip/*.xpi/build dirs) + scratch/runtime (_paste*.json, tmp_session_start, .session_counts) as "not state"; report only. `touch_start` — touch /home/claude/tmp_session_start; mtime_output. `session_time` — diff tmp_session_start→now as "Session time: Xm Ys". `touch_chat_start` — touch outputs/tmp_chat_start; mtime_output (orphaned; prefer touch_start). `chat_time` — diff outputs/tmp_chat_start as "Chat time: Xm Ys". `session_time_header` — silently at start of every response: diff tmp_session_start, print "⏱ Session: Xm Ys"; skip if file missing.

**Output modifiers:** `dont_narrate_fixes` — no fix narration. `skip_post-round_summary` — no summary. `no_fix_list` — no fix list before files. `showme` — present modified output files with MDT mtimes. `showmeall` — present all output files with MDT mtimes. `jump-to-bottom` — jump to bottom. `cleanstop` — if clean stop, else showme; jump-to-bottom.

**Single-shot:** `review` — report all issues, no fixes. `linesme` — line count. `timeout_sleep_ints` — verify timeout/sleep vars are integers; no-op otherwise. `fiximportant` — fix topmost remaining issue. `sequential-fixes` — loop (above). `rewrite` — (1) timeout_sleep_ints (2) fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent (3) linesme. `otf` — confirm one-true-file active. `do_acid` — activate ACID from `claude_acid_2.md`; if absent locally, fetch from `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/levitation29/claude/refs/heads/main/claude_acid_2.md` silently and save to `/home/claude/claude_acid_2.md`; snapshot all /home/claude/ files lacking one, register default invariants, confirm; if already active re-snapshot and re-confirm; follow SNAPSHOT/EDIT/PUBLISH/RESTORE. `trim_for_preferences` — read `command_2.notes` (uploads or working path); produce a condensed paste-ready version (strip prose/motivation/examples/cross-session blocks; bold inline section labels; one terse line per command); save `command_2_preferences.notes`, publish to outputs.

**Workers:** `fix-silent` — fix all bugs silently. `fix-broad-silent` — fix-silent + style/naming/comments/dead code. `fix-security-silent` — fix injection/privilege/leakage/unsafe silently. `fix-perf-review-silent` — perf-expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `fix-api-review-silent` — API-expert review, flag issues, then sequential-fixes. `md-update-silent` — update .md with impl details (esp. error handling), then sequential-fixes. `schema-update-silent` — update .schema with full SQL behavior range, then sequential-fixes. `fix-rewrite-silent` — rewrite unclean sections, no commentary. `fix-rewrite-keepcomments-silent` — same, keep all comments.

**Counters:** `session_counts` — read/increment turn count in /home/claude/.session_counts (`turns tools`), write back, print "🔢 Turn N · tool calls so far: C". `session_counts_header` — silently run session_counts at start of every response, print result first; skip if unwritable. `session_counts_resync T C` — write "T C" to .session_counts directly; both args required. `xyzzy` — touch_start; session_time_header; session_counts; session_counts_header. Tool call must be literally the first thing in the response, no text before it.

**HUD audit (claude_browser_extension.sh):** `hud_audit` — paste a `_claudeDebug.audit()` snapshot; persist to /home/claude/hud_ledger.json (create + announce if missing; else append as next `entry`, bump `next_entry`); after each write `cp` → outputs/hud_ledger.json; treat that file as authoritative history — flatten all `entries[].snapshot.data`, dedup rows by `id`, assess the new paste vs all stored history (TTFT, total time, tok/s, output size, thinking-vs-answer share, stop reasons, error/limit signals); also append an in-conversation numbered entry mirroring the file `entry`; flag drift and outliers; correlations not proof; at session start, if ledger absent rebuild from any uploaded hud_ledger.json, else start fresh at entry 1.

**Session resume:** Projects don't accept/auto-extract `.zip` — persist files INDIVIDUALLY in the Project's Files section (they appear at /mnt/project/<name> next chat); a `.zip` is usable only attached to a chat (→ /mnt/user-data/uploads/, unzip there). md5 = change-detection. `resume_seed` — write `resume_seed.md` (one-true path, publish to outputs); facts only from real files/this session, never invent; five literal-heading sections `resume` parses — **RESUME** (one line: resuming; session start = touch_start + counters; follow command system; for any command not in live prefs use attached `command_2_preferences.notes`); **MANIFEST** (table, one row per state file: `working_name | store_as | role | required|optional | origin(project|upload|session) | modified(y/n) | bytes | lines | md5`; add stale /mnt/project md5 when origin=project & modified=y; exclude regenerable `.zip`/`.xpi`; `store_as` renames odd extensions to .md/.txt/.json); **LEDGER** (if `hud_ledger.json` is state: entries, unique rows by id, id list, next entry); **STATE** (done edits; OPEN items; DONE one-offs); **START** (run `resume`). `resume` — run FIRST in a new chat: (1) `touch_start` + counters; (2) read MANIFEST/LEDGER/STATE/START from pasted seed or uploaded `resume_seed.md`; (3) locate each file: /mnt/project/<store_as>, then /mnt/user-data/uploads/ (incl. extracting an uploaded `.zip`), then working paths — never seek a `.zip` in /mnt/project; (4) md5sum + compare → ✓match / ⚠mismatch ("equals known-stale" when so) / ✗absent; (5) on any required ⚠/✗ STOP + print upload checklist (filename + why), never accept md5≠manifest, no proceed unless user says "proceed degraded"; (6) confirm ✓/✗ table and await next command — NEVER cp any file to a working path during resume; user sets up one-true-file when starting work; blind cp could overwrite a fresher upload.

**unzip-project** — (1) Scan /mnt/user-data/uploads/ for `*_YYYY-MM-DD_v<N>.zip`; select most recent by date, highest `_v<N>` as tiebreaker. (2) If /mnt/project/ is non-empty: warn and ask — wipe (delete all first) or overwrite (same paths only)? If overwrite: list all paths inside the zip; if any file's relative path differs only in top-level folder from an existing file in /mnt/project/ with the same basename → abort with conflict report. (3) Confirm: "Unzip `<file>` to /mnt/project/ [wipe first / overwrite]?" — await y/n. (4) On y: wipe if chosen (`rm -rf /mnt/project/*`), then `unzip -o <path> -d /mnt/project/`. (5) If tiers landed under a single top-level wrapper dir (usual — the export carries its own folder, so /mnt/project/<wrapper>/tier1_live_state/... not /mnt/project/tier1_live_state/...): note `resume` expects files flat at /mnt/project/<store_as> and SUGGEST the user run `flatten.sh here` (the unified flattener, replaces flatten_v.sh + flatten_mnt_project.sh; tier-merges into /mnt/project/: tier1 contents + tier2 WHOLE-DIR (root .md specs → root, scripts/ & narrative/ as subdirs) + tier3 contents; overwrite-same-name, never delete; prompts before removing the wrapper; ends with showmyfs); do NOT auto-run — await user. (6) `showmyfs`.
